<white>synopsys:</>
    the command <green>mkdir</> is used to create a folder (category) in the 
    database filesystem ( of the website ).
    
    <light_gray>this command has a command alias, called </><green>md</>
    
<white>usage: </><green>mkdir</> <cyan>$path_to_object</>
       <green>md</> <cyan>$path_to_object</>

<white>arguments:</>
    <cyan>$path_to_object</> - mandatory argument, representing either a
        relative path, either a full path to the object (directory /
        category).

<white>important:</>
    <red>!</> this command requires a website context. for more
      information see command <green>use</>

<white>examples:</>
    <green>mkdir</> <cyan>foo</>
    <green>mkdir</> <cyan>../bar</>
